canvas { display:block; }
</style></head><body><div class="container"><header><h1>Campervan HQ & Van Land</h1><h2>Retail Support Metrics</h2><h3>Q1 2026</h3></header><div class="kpi-grid-4"><div class="kpi primary"><div class="number">1,752</div><div class="label">Real Tickets</div></div><div class="kpi success"><div class="number">84%</div><div class="label">Human Closed</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="number" style="color:#7c3aed">16%</div><div class="label">AI Bot Closed</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="number" style="color:#94a3b8">739</div><div class="label">Auto Filtered (spam)</div></div></div>
<div class="kpi-grid-3"><div class="kpi success"><div class="number">4.87</div><div class="label">Avg Human CSAT</div></div><div class="kpi alert"><div class="number">3.67</div><div class="label">AI Bot CSAT</div></div><div class="kpi success"><div class="number">6m 20s</div><div class="label">Avg First Response (Q1)</div></div></div>
<div class="kpi-grid-4"><div class="kpi warn"><div class="number">~33%</div><div class="label">WISMO (of real volume)</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="number" style="color:#e11d48">Order ETA</div><div class="label">#1 Reason — 354 tickets</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="number" style="color:#7c3aed">Window</div><div class="label">#1 Product — 276 tickets</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="number" style="color:#0d9488">EcoFlow</div><div class="label">#1 Vendor — 145 tickets</div></div></div>
<div class="kpi-grid-4" style="margin-bottom:30px"><div class="kpi primary"><div class="number">765</div><div class="label">Pre-Sale Tickets</div></div><div class="kpi"><div class="number" style="color:#6366f1">Email 51%</div><div class="label">Top Channel — 1,666 tickets</div></div><div class="kpi warn"><div class="number">1.75</div><div class="label">Msgs / Ticket (avg 4.15)</div></div><div class="kpi success"><div class="number">21m</div><div class="label">Chat Resolution Time</div></div></div><div class="card"><h2>How We Compare — Gorgias Benchmarks</h2><p style="color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:16px;">Lifetime data across all teams/queues vs. other Gorgias merchants</p><table><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Us</th><th>Avg Merchant</th><th>Top 5%</th><th>Status</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>CSAT</td><td>4.85</td><td>4.56</td><td>4.89</td><td><span class="compare-good">Good — near Top 5%</span></td></tr><tr><td>Resolution Time</td><td>16h 05m</td><td>1d 17h</td><td>2h 11m</td><td><span class="compare-good">Good — room to improve toward Top 5%</span></td></tr><tr><td>Messages per Ticket</td><td>6.26</td><td>4.15</td><td>3.1</td><td><span class="compare-warn">Needs work — 50% more msgs than avg</span></td></tr><tr><td>First Response Time</td><td>6m 11s</td><td>10h 28m</td><td>46m 06s</td><td><span class="compare-great">Exceptional</span></td></tr><tr><td>AI Handoff Response</td><td>36m 18s</td><td>10h 28m</td><td>46m 06s</td><td><span class="compare-great">Exceptional</span></td></tr></tbody></table><div class="insight good">First response time is a standout strength — 6 minutes vs industry average of 10+ hours. The main opportunity lies in reducing back-and-forth and tightening processes around common order-status and pre-sale questions.</div></div><div class="card"><h2>The #1 Finding: WISMO is 33% of Real Support Volume</h2><div class="insight critical">~571 tickets in Q1 are customers asking order-status / lead-time questions — the single biggest operational support burden.</div><div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-top: 16px;"><div><h3>WISMO-Related Reasons</h3><table><tr><td>Order ETA / Status</td><td>354</td></tr><tr><td>Availability / Lead Time</td><td>154</td></tr><tr><td>Shipping Speed / Timing</td><td>63</td></tr><tr><th>Total WISMO-Related</th><th>~571</th></tr></table></div><div><div class="chart-container"><canvas id="wismoChart"></canvas></div></div></div></div><div class="card"><h2>Agent Performance — Retail Team</h2><p style="color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:16px;">Jeremy's primary volume is in Shopify Inbox (not reflected here).</p><table><thead><tr><th>Agent</th><th>Role</th><th>% CSR</th><th>Closed</th><th>Handle Time</th><th>CSAT</th><th>1st Response</th><th>One-Touch %</th><th>Closed/Hr</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Ellie</td><td><span class="badge badge-t2">T2</span></td><td></td><td>858</td><td>9m 23s</td><td>4.88</td><td>1h 12m</td><td>23.08%</td><td>3.93</td></tr><tr><td>Josie</td><td><span class="badge badge-t2">T2</span></td><td>50%</td><td>511</td><td>6m 57s</td><td>4.83</td><td>1h 31m</td><td>26.03%</td><td>5.97</td></tr><tr><td>AI Bot</td><td><span class="badge badge-ai">AI</span></td><td></td><td>377</td><td>2m 18s</td><td>3.67</td><td>17s</td><td>61.54%</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Holly</td><td><span class="badge badge-t3">T3 / Mgr</span></td><td></td><td>251</td><td>7m 32s</td><td>4.81</td><td>1h 50m</td><td>29.08%</td><td>3.42</td></tr><tr><td>Garrett</td><td><span class="badge badge-t3">T3 / PM</span></td><td>10-15%</td><td>163</td><td>5m 03s</td><td>5</td><td>1h 20m</td><td>—</td><td>10.56</td></tr><tr><td>Kelsey</td><td><span class="badge badge-t3">T3 / Mktg</span></td><td>30%</td><td>105</td><td>31m 55s</td><td>5</td><td>17h 49m</td><td>21.90%</td><td>1.56</td></tr><tr><td>Jeremy</td><td><span class="badge badge-t3">T3 / E-com Mgr</span></td><td></td><td>41</td><td>8m 45s</td><td>4.6</td><td>9h 35m</td><td>12.20%</td><td>2.51</td></tr></tbody></table><div class="chart-container tall" style="margin-top:20px"><canvas id="agentChart"></canvas></div></div><div class="card"><h2>Channel Mix</h2><div class="chart-row"><div><table><thead><tr><th>Channel</th><th>Tickets</th><th>% Mix</th><th>Resolution</th><th>1st Response</th><th>CSAT</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Email</td><td>1,666</td><td>51.5%</td><td>3d 14h</td><td>3h 47m</td><td>4.93</td></tr><tr><td>Chat</td><td>824</td><td>25.4%</td><td>21m 27s</td><td>17s</td><td>4.77</td></tr><tr><td>Phone</td><td>358</td><td>11.1%</td><td>23h 25m</td><td>2h 50m</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>SMS</td><td>222</td><td>6.9%</td><td>19h 55m</td><td>23m 54s</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td>Help Center</td><td>107</td><td>3.3%</td><td>2d 06h</td><td>2h 12m</td><td>4.68</td></tr><tr><td>Contact Form</td><td>61</td><td>1.9%</td><td>3h 07m</td><td>36m 54s</td><td>4.64</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div><div class="chart-container"><canvas id="channelChart"></canvas></div></div></div><div class="insight">Chat is the speed champion — fastest first response and fastest resolution. Email carries the most volume and the strongest CSAT, but it is by far the slowest to resolve.</div></div><div class="card"><h2>Busiest Times — Ticket Volume Heatmap</h2><p style="color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:16px;">Darker = more tickets created. Peak: Mon 10 AM (103 tickets in Q1).</p><div style="overflow-x:auto;"><table class="heatmap" id="heatmapTable"><thead><tr><th>Hour</th><th>Mon</th><th>Tue</th><th>Wed</th><th>Thu</th><th>Fri</th><th>Sat</th><th>Sun</th></tr></thead><tbody id="heatmapBody"></tbody></table></div><div class="insight">Staffing insight: 90% of volume is Mon–Fri, with the peak window 8 AM–12 PM. Monday 9–11 AM is the single busiest block. Weekends drop 72%.</div></div><div class="chart-row"><div class="card"><h2>Top Product Categories</h2><p style="color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:12px;">By ticket count (excluding spam, dropped, dev/test, and No Product)</p><div class="chart-container tall"><canvas id="productChart"></canvas></div></div><div class="card"><h2>Top Vendors</h2><p style="color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:12px;">By ticket count (excluding No Vendor, untagged, and dropped)</p><div class="chart-container tall"><canvas id="vendorChart"></canvas></div></div></div><div class="insight">Total <strong>Other Vendor</strong> = 356. That is large enough to limit the usefulness of vendor reporting, so it would be worthwhile to add more granular vendor options to the Ticket Fields in Gorgias. Product Misc also accounts for 81 tickets, which may be worth reviewing if more specific product categories would improve reporting.</div><div class="card"><h2>Top Ticket Reasons</h2><p style="color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:12px;">Excluding spam, dropped, and dev/test tickets</p><div class="chart-container tall"><canvas id="reasonChart"></canvas></div></div><div class="card"><h2>Vendor Support Burden — Accountability Scorecard</h2><p style="color:var(--muted); margin-bottom:16px;">Vendors tiered by support ticket volume. Revenue data is still needed to calculate support-cost-per-revenue ratios.</p><h3>High Burden (75+ tickets/quarter) — 4 vendors, 467 tickets</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Vendor</th><th>Q1 Tickets</th><th>% of Tagged</th><th>Tickets/Week</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="tier-high"><td>EcoFlow</td><td>145</td><td>14.2%</td><td>11.2</td></tr><tr class="tier-high"><td>Perfect Fit</td><td>125</td><td>12.2%</td><td>9.6</td></tr><tr class="tier-high"><td>CR Laurence</td><td>109</td><td>10.6%</td><td>8.4</td></tr><tr class="tier-high"><td>Van Windows Direct</td><td>88</td><td>8.6%</td><td>6.8</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Medium Burden (30–74 tickets/quarter) — 5 vendors, 222 tickets</h3><table><thead><tr><th>Vendor</th><th>Q1 Tickets</th><th>% of Tagged</th><th>Tickets/Week</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="tier-med"><td>Fiamma</td><td>66</td><td>6.4%</td><td>5.1</td></tr><tr class="tier-med"><td>2tec2</td><td>52</td><td>5.1%</td><td>4.0</td></tr><tr class="tier-med"><td>Marathon</td><td>42</td><td>4.1%</td><td>3.2</td></tr><tr class="tier-med"><td>Tec Vanlife</td><td>32</td><td>3.1%</td><td>2.5</td></tr><tr class="tier-med"><td>Lonseal</td><td>30</td><td>2.9%</td><td>2.3</td></tr></tbody></table><p style="color:var(--muted); margin-top:12px;"><em>32 additional vendors in Low tier (&lt;30 tickets/quarter) account for 335 tickets combined.</em></p><div class="insight">Vendor burden is concentrated. A relatively small set of vendors accounts for a disproportionate share of support demand, which makes this a strong candidate for revenue cross-reference, supplier conversations, and product-page improvements.</div></div><div class="card"><h2>Pre-Sale Opportunity</h2><div class="insight good">765 pre-sale tickets = customers actively trying to buy.</div><table><thead><tr><th>Pre-Sale Reason</th><th>Q1 Tickets</th><th>Opportunity</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Product Questions</td><td>342</td><td>FAQ pages, AI bot, comparison guides</td></tr><tr><td>Ordering / Website Help</td><td>166</td><td>UX improvements, checkout flow</td></tr><tr><td>Availability / Lead Time</td><td>154</td><td>Stock status on product pages</td></tr><tr><td>Shipping Questions</td><td>27</td><td>Shipping calculator, clear policies</td></tr><tr><td>Coupon / Discount</td><td>29</td><td>Promo visibility, exit-intent</td></tr><tr><td>Installation Questions</td><td>36</td><td>Install guides, video content</td></tr><tr><td>MOV</td><td>11</td><td>Minimum-order clarity on site</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class="card"><h2>Dropped Calls Analysis</h2><div class="insight critical">180 dropped calls in Q1 — all from CVHQ. Van Land answered 327 calls. Combined, 507 call attempts — 36% of callers never got through.</div><table><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Van Land — Connected Calls</td><td>327</td></tr><tr><td>CVHQ — Dropped Calls</td><td>180</td></tr><tr><td>Total Call Attempts</td><td>507</td></tr><tr><td>Drop Rate (CVHQ share of attempts)</td><td>36%</td></tr><tr><td>Avg Dropped per Week</td><td>~14</td></tr></tbody></table><p style="margin-top:12px;">CSR time estimate: At roughly the observed phone handle time, answering these calls would require approximately 33 hours per quarter.</p></div><div class="card"><h2>Top 6 Recommendations for Q2</h2><ol class="rec-list"><li><strong>Improve AI Bot CSAT & Expand Scope</strong><br>Current CSAT 3.67 vs human 4.87 — focus training on product knowledge and common inquiries to both improve satisfaction and increase the share of tickets AI can handle. Target: 4.3+ CSAT, 20%+ of ticket volume. <em>Frees CSR time for pre-sale conversion and phone support evaluation.</em></li><li><strong>Attack WISMO — Streamline Order Tracking</strong><br>WISMO remains one of the largest support burdens in the report. Build an order status page, add realistic ETAs by product type, and start tracking actual vs promised vendor delivery times. Streamlining the process also enables AI to eventually handle the bulk of WISMO inquiries. <em>Frees CSR time for pre-sale conversion and phone support evaluation.</em></li><li><strong>Convert Pre-Sale Tickets into Revenue</strong><br>Pre-sale tickets = customers actively trying to buy. Track conversion rate separately. Route to trained agents. Better product pages (FAQs, install guides, stock status) reduce questions AND increase sales.</li><li><strong>Phone Channel Decision</strong><br>Van Land answers calls; CVHQ drops a meaningful share of them. A notable slice of those callers are likely pre-sale inquiries — potential buyers who never connect. Evaluate whether adding phone/callback support for CVHQ would pay for itself in captured sales.</li><li><strong>Vendor Accountability Scorecard</strong><br>A small number of vendors generate a disproportionate share of support tickets. Cross-reference with Shopify revenue to calculate support cost per revenue dollar. Use in vendor negotiations and stocking decisions — hold vendors accountable for the support burden their products create.</li><li><strong>Close the Tagging Gap</strong><br>"Other" appears across reason, product, and vendor fields — these are tickets where more granular tags are needed. Better tagging = better data = smarter decisions. Review and expand tag taxonomy to reduce "Other" classification.</li></ol></div><footer>Campervan HQ & Van Land · Q1 2026 Retail Support Analysis · Data source: Gorgias</footer></div><script>
const colors={ blue:'#3b82f6', amber:'#f59e0b', red:'#ef4444', green:'#10b981', purple:'#8b5cf6', pink:'#ec4899', indigo:'#6366f1', teal:'#14b8a6', orange:'#f97316', slate:'#64748b' };
